We have been watching it ever since we got it. They really did pick the best of the Abby episodes.

For you special fans of Pauley Parrette as forensics goth goddess Abby on NCIS, here's a treat.  Twelve episodes, specially picked from the many seasons of NCIS, all featuring Abby in a prominent role.  The twelve episodes are all good ones, and the collection is a nice retrospective on the changing casting at NCIS (remember Gerald, Ducky's assistant from the very first season, or Sasha Alexander, now on Rizzoli and Isles, from the first two seasons?).  Among the best: the Halloween episode in which Abby channels Marilyn Monroe.  The package includes commentary for a few of the episodes, along with a featurette on the character of Abby.  Recommended.

I wanted to write a review because Amazon had no details on this product. I purchased it because I like NCIS and Abby is my wife's favorite character, so it gives us some great episodes to enjoy together.

There are 12 fan chosen episodes across 3 discs, all introduced by Pauley Perrette herself. There is also a special featurette called from Pauley to Abby: hairspray, lipstick, and tattoos.

The included episodes are:
Bte noire
Swak
Bloodbath
Witch hunt
Cover story
Dog tags
Toxic
Cracked
Enemy on the hill
Up in smoke
Recovery
Hit and run
